 flat actuation response up to 10 MHz is\nachieved. We leverage this capability to demonstrate a compact coherent LiDAR\nengine that can generate up to 800 kHz FMCW triangular optical chirp signals,\nrequiring neither any active linearization nor predistortion compensation, and\nperform a 10 m optical ranging experiment, with a resolution of 12.5 cm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Apr 2021 08:38:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Jul 2021 12:08:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-16"}
