rbulent velocity, $\\xi$, of coronal\nrain clumps and off-limb spicules present in the same data set, and we have\nfound that the former ones have narrower T and $\\xi$ distributions, their\naverage temperature is similar, and coronal rain has microturbulent velocities\nsmaller than those of spicules\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Apr 2021 12:26:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-09"}
